amorn-dtsm/ai_assistant — FORK BUILD MARKER
============================================

Presence of this file tells deploy-image.ps1 that the current build tree is the
CUSTOMIZED FORK, not stock upstream (Mintplex-Labs/anything-llm).

deploy-image.ps1 refuses to build/ship the `ai-assistant:latest` image unless
this file exists in the build context. A raw upstream/stock checkout does not
have this file, so it can never accidentally overwrite the production image with
a feature-less stock build.

WHY A MARKER INSTEAD OF A FEATURE LIST
--------------------------------------
The guard is intentionally FEATURE-AGNOSTIC. Do NOT list individual features
(source-viewer, LINE channel, etc.) in the guard — that would force you to edit
the guard every time you add a feature, and would wrongly block deploying a
branch that has one feature but not another.

Instead: this single marker is committed once to the fork base branch and is
inherited by every feature branch built on top of it. Add as many features as
you like — you never touch the guard or this file again.

DO NOT DELETE. DO NOT COMMIT THIS FILE TO THE UPSTREAM REMOTE.
